article.description: — Ryan Schwieger had 22 points as Loyola Chicago topped Illinois-Chicago 80-63 on Saturday.
article.headline: Schwieger scores 22 to lift Loyola Chicago over UIC 80-63
article.linkText: Schwieger scores 22 to lift Loyola Chicago over UIC 80-63
article.story: CHICAGO -- — Ryan Schwieger had 22 points as Loyola Chicago topped Illinois-Chicago 80-63 on Saturday. Lucas Williamson had 16 points and six rebounds for Loyola Chicago (4-0). Braden Norris added 12 points. Tate Hall had eight rebounds. Damaria Franklin had 22 points and 12 rebounds for the Flames (2-2). Jalen Warren added 13 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
